 coords 4119.81 150.429 6418.823
 m_iTimeLimitMinutes 65
 m_aMissionDescriptors {
  CRF_MissionDescriptor "{644250503DF684C0}" {
   m_sTextData "Blufor is conducting a large scale operation in this AO. There are three primary stages to their plan. First, they have identified AA defences in zone 1 that need to be destroyed. Second, there is a fuel depot in zone 2 that they will need to locate and destroy. Finally, they will need to locate and destroy the enemy HQ in zone 3. Blufor will respawn in waves, and receive tickets for each objective destroyed. Opfor will fully respawn when an objective is destroyed."\
   ""\
   "BLUFOR Comp: Air Assault"\
   "BLUFOR Assets: Unarmed UH60s"\
   ""\
   "OPFOR Comp: Armored"\
   "OPFOR Assets: T-72s, Mortars, Constructable Defenses"\
   ""\
   "Time: 65 min"\
   "Weather: Cloudy"
  }
  CRF_MissionDescriptor "{64425051F2E00216}" {
   m_sTextData "Each zone has an objective to destroy. In each, place a bomb on the tan supply crates near the objective. This is the trigger for the objective destruction. You will receive tickets on obj destruction. Additionally, you start with all the assets you will receive for the match at the beginning. Do not field more assets than you have speciality leads for them. You have been given a logi lead slot to help facilitate troop reinforcement."\
   ""\
   "Zone 1: ZU-23 emplacement"\
   "Zone 2: Fuel Depot"\
   "Zone 3: Enemy HQ"
  }
  CRF_MissionDescriptor "{64425051B9B5AF67}" {
   m_sTextData "Each zone has an objective to protect. In each, the objective trigger is the tan supply boxes near the objective feature. On obj destruction, Opfor will fully respawn after ten seconds. You start with all the assets you will receive for the match at the beginning. Do not field more assets than you have speciality leads for them."\
   ""\
   "Zone 1: ZU-23 emplacement"\
   "Zone 2: Fuel Depot"\
   "Zone 3: Enemy HQ"
  }
  CRF_MissionDescriptor "{6442505149CF6C93}" {
   m_sTextData "Blufor has half of their slotted units in tickets at the beginning of the match. For each destroyed objective, they will receive that number of tickets."\
   ""\
   "Opfor fully respawns 10 seconds after an objective is destroyed. This gives time for downed people to respawn, and not miss the respawn wave."\
   ""\
   "Each zone will unlock 2 minutes after objective destruction."
  }
 }
